item.title: Help (Urgent)
item.dc:creator: @Killerswan Killerswan
item.description:
@Killerswan wrote:

Okay it’s easy ill help ya out, First go to your modem on your browser,

type something like:

http://67.247.64.1

Once your on your modem page look for something that relates to port forwarding, (mine actually says portforwarding.)
Start a new port forward use these as your guide:

 Port start/in - 43594
 Port End/out - 43594
 IP - 64.247.76.11
 Name - (name it anything you want)
 Type - TCP or both

Click active and click apply, and then add an exception in your firewall.
